8.6 added significant function, such that 8.5.1 may be the highest level
which certain programs or hardware might work.

The PC Compatibility card was supported at the 8.5 level ONLY with a
patch, so 8.1 is its last official support point. Once the software for
that card was spun-off to a Canadian company, software support beyond
8.1/8.5.1 was released, including at least 8.6, and possibly 9.0.

So, it may be good to have both 8.5.1 and 8.6, and then test everything
on each, and fall back to 8.5.1 only if you have issues with 8.6.

My original Gossamer, still operational, still has 8.6.

My later Gossamers, all now removed from service, have 9.2.1.
