You'd want to install 8.0 for PPC only. That
eliminates installing any 68K code with functions
duplicated by PPC code when installing for any Mac.
However, there's still 68K code in the System.

What I don't know is if the 8.1 update converts a PPC
only 8.0 install to a Fat install that'll boot an 040.

That's always been the main thing I don't like about
updates from 8.0 to 8.1, 8.5 to 8.6 and the 9.x.x
series. It's useless to do a custom install of the
starting version because the updaters don't allow you
to choose what NOT to install, so you end up having to
manually delete things for stuff your Mac doesn't
have.

A 75Mhz computer, no matter what kind it is, won't
give the impression of being slow on the net, it will
be slow on the net. :P It should be tolerable for
e-mail, especially on DSL or other broadband, but
loading websites is not going to be speedy, due a lot
to how un-optimized most web browsers are. They're
like most other apps these days, relying on sheer CPU
grunt power and lots of RAM to hide how bloated and
slow at page rendering they are.

