While a 7300, 7500, 7600 and all 85xx, 86xx, 95xx and 96xx machines can
take 7200 RAM, the reverse is not true.

The 7200 must have FPM RAM, never EDO RAM.

And, while the Apple Network Server spec says the ANS must have FPM RAM
(and that it must be parity), the ANS will accept EDO as if it was FPM
(as will the 9500, from which it was designed), and it will accept
non-parity RAM, too. But, just one stick of non-parity RAM turns off
parity checking for all RAM.
